        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 29 at 3:47PM MDT until June 29 at 4:30PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>SVRBOU

The National Weather Service in Denver has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Larimer County in north central Colorado...
Northwest Boulder and Northeast Boulder County in northeastern
Colorado...

* Until 430 PM MDT.

* At 347 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Drake, or 19
miles southwest of Fort Collins, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect
hail damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.
Expect wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Southwestern Loveland, Berthoud, Lyons, Carter Lake, Cedar Cove,
Pinewood Springs, Drake and Campion.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds and large
hail.</instruction>
